entry.title: tote tour: Only show nudge to new users
entry.content:
Uses the existing apis in ash/user_education and logic similar to

Welcome Tour to limit the nudge to users new to ChromeOS. Also uses

the new pref created for this purpose to persist this eligibility

across restarts since the nudge may not be triggered in the first

session.



This involved moving the `NudgeShouldBeShown()` definition inside

a class so that the user education api key could be passed to it.



Also incidentally fixes another holding space wallpaper nudge test

that had a flaw exposed by this change.

entry.title: MessagePumpEpoll: Attempt more works only on valid epoll events.
entry.content:
epoll_wait will always report for EPOLLERR and EPOLLHUP, even if don't

explicitly request them in the events argument[1].



Errors in watched file descriptors cause persistent EPOLLHUP

notifications. The repeated EPOLLHUP notifications will trigger the run

loop to set `processed_events`, but lacking valid `DoWork` leads to a

deadlock.



This CL improves the disconnected file descriptor handling. Upon

detecting a disconnection, notify all associated watchers to gracefully

stop watching; If no active watchers, the file descriptor is removed

from the epoll interest list. It prevents the unconditionally epoll_wait

return.



This CL also replicates code from `MessagePumpLibevent` to attempt more

works only when triggered by valid epoll events.



[1] epoll_ctl(2) - Linux manual page

https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/epoll_ctl.2.html

entry.title: gpu: Make integration test CheckSwapChainHasAlpha require trace event
entry.content:
Previously,

gpu_tests.trace_integration_test.TraceIntegrationTest.SwapChainTraceTest_IsOpaque

only checked if there was no event that matches

_PRESENT_SWAP_CHAIN_EVENT_NAME and also contains a has_alpha value that

is unexpected.



This means the test could still pass even if there were no trace events

with the expected name at all or no events that have a valid has_alpha

value.



This CL changes the test to fail if we see none of the expected

events, which should catch regressions that can be caused by renaming

or updating the TRACE_EVENT call on the C++ side.

entry.title: v4l2: CENCv1 H264 support in V4L2
entry.content:
This adds handling of CENCv1 H264 encrypted streams to V4L2. This uses

the existing functionality for handling this in H264Decoder but also

adds a parameter so the secure_handle gets passed into the accelerator

as well.



The accelerator will invoke a Mojo IPC call with the relevant contents

from the SPS/PPS, the associated secure handle and an offset. It will

receive back success/failure and the required contents from H264 slice

header parsing in the secure world. Decoding then resumes with that

slice header information.
